2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper proposes a framework for generating 3D models, which is a common topic in computer graphics. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper mentions the efficiency of the proposed method, which could be relevant in robotics applications. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the problem of depth estimation in low-textured areas, which is a common problem in multimedia applications such as video processing. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a probabilistic graphical model, which is a common tool in machine learning, to embed planar models into PatchMatch multi-view stereo.
